      "text": "How YouTube Calculates Creator Revenue"
    },
    {
      "id": "t34",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "YouTube uses two key metrics:"
    },
    {
      "id": "t35",
      "tag": "strong",
      "text": "CPM"
    },
    {
      "id": "t36",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "(Cost Per Mille — what advertisers pay per 1,000 ad impressions) and"
    },
    {
      "id": "t37",
      "tag": "strong",
      "text": "RPM"
    },
    {
      "id": "t38",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "(Revenue Per Mille — what you actually receive per 1,000 views). YouTube keeps approximately 45% of ad revenue, so your RPM is roughly 55% of your CPM."
    },
    {
      "id": "t39",
      "tag": "strong",
      "text": "Formula: RPM = CPM × 0.55 × monetization rate"
    },
    {
      "id": "t40",
      "tag": "p",
      "text": "— Not every view serves an ad. Your effective monetization rate is typically 70–90%."
    },
